---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Accounting, Tax & Compliance | ARM Management"
  description="Monthly bookkeeping, VAT returns, corporate tax filings, and statutory accounts across multiple jurisdictions through a single senior relationship."
>
<main>

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero__bg" style="background-image:url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1554224154-26032ffc0d07?w=1600&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop')"></div>
    <div class="page-hero__overlay"></div>
    <div class="page-hero__content container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Accounting &amp; Tax</span>
      <h1>Accounting, Tax &amp;<br>Monthly Compliance</h1>
      <p>One relationship. All jurisdictions. Every deadline met.</p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="justify-content:flex-start;margin-top:30px">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Speak With a Senior Advisor →</a>
        <a href="/insights" class="btn-secondary">Read Our Insights</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--cream">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal">What We Do</span>
      <h2 class="reveal">A Single Relationship Across Every Jurisdiction</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule reveal"></div>
      <p class="reveal">Managing accounting and tax compliance across multiple jurisdictions is one of the most operationally demanding aspects of running an international business. Deadlines, reporting formats, VAT regimes, and audit requirements vary dramatically — and the consequences of missed filings extend beyond penalties to damaged banking relationships and regulatory standing.</p>
      <p class="reveal" style="margin-top:20px">ARM Management offers a single relationship: one senior contact who coordinates local accountants and tax advisors across all your jurisdictions, ensures nothing is missed, and translates local compliance requirements into actionable management information you can actually use.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--warm" style="border-top:1px solid #E2DDD6">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal">Our Services</span>
      <h2 class="reveal">What We Handle</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule reveal"></div>
      <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:40px">
        <div class="card reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <h3>Monthly Bookkeeping</h3>
          <p>Recording and reconciling transactions across jurisdictions. Maintaining compliant accounting records in local format and currency, with management accounts prepared to a consistent standard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <h3>VAT &amp; Indirect Tax Returns</h3>
          <p>Preparing and filing VAT, GST, and indirect tax returns across all operating jurisdictions. Includes EU VAT OSS management, EORI registration, and intrastat reporting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <h3>Corporate Tax Filings</h3>
          <p>Annual corporate tax return preparation, transfer pricing documentation, and coordination with local tax advisors for complex cross-border structures.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <h3>Financial Statements</h3>
          <p>Preparing statutory financial statements compliant with local GAAP requirements — IFRS, UK GAAP, Dutch GAAP, and others — coordinated with local auditors where required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <h3>Payroll Tax Compliance</h3>
          <p>Employer registrations, monthly payroll tax filings, and year-end returns across all jurisdictions with employees or directors on local payroll.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <h3>Tax Advisory</h3>
          <p>Strategic advice on corporate tax structure, treaty benefits, VAT planning, and cross-border tax efficiency — delivered by advisors who understand the commercial context, not just the rules.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--navy">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal" style="color:#B8960C">The ARM Approach</span>
      <h2 class="reveal" style="color:#F7F3EC">Compliance Without the Complexity.</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule reveal"></div>
      <p class="reveal" style="color:rgba(247,243,236,.78)">Most accounting firms are organised by country. You engage a firm in each jurisdiction, manage multiple relationships, reconcile conflicting advice, and still risk gaps between entities. ARM Management reverses this model: one senior advisor holds the complete picture of your group structure and coordinates all local professionals on your behalf.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:48px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:32px">
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="border-top:1px solid rgba(184,150,12,.3);padding-top:20px"><h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B8960C;margin-bottom:10px">Deadline Ownership</h4><p style="color:rgba(247,243,236,.65);font-size:15px;line-height:1.75">We track every filing deadline across every jurisdiction you operate in. You will not discover a missed VAT return from a penalty notice.</p></div>
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="border-top:1px solid rgba(184,150,12,.3);padding-top:20px"><h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B8960C;margin-bottom:10px">Local Expertise, Central Coordination</h4><p style="color:rgba(247,243,236,.65);font-size:15px;line-height:1.75">We work with vetted local accountants and tax advisors in each jurisdiction — selected for track record — coordinated through a single ARM relationship.</p></div>
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="border-top:1px solid rgba(184,150,12,.3);padding-top:20px"><h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B8960C;margin-bottom:10px">Consistent Management Reporting</h4><p style="color:rgba(247,243,236,.65);font-size:15px;line-height:1.75">Local statutory accounts vary in format. ARM produces consistent consolidated management information so you can make decisions, not just satisfy regulators.</p></div>
        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="border-top:1px solid rgba(184,150,12,.3);padding-top:20px"><h4 style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#B8960C;margin-bottom:10px">Transparent Fixed Fees</h4><p style="color:rgba(247,243,236,.65);font-size:15px;line-height:1.75">Monthly compliance fees are fixed and agreed in advance by jurisdiction. No hourly billing surprises at year-end.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--cream" style="border-top:1px solid #E2DDD6">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal">Jurisdictions</span>
      <h2 class="reveal">Where We File</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule reveal"></div>
      <div class="reveal" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:24px;margin-top:32px">
        <div style="padding:24px;background:#FDFAF6;border:1px solid #E2DDD6;border-radius:2px"><h4 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px">European Union</h4><p style="font-size:14px;color:#6B7280;line-height:1.65">All 27 member states plus UK and Switzerland. VAT OSS, corporate tax, statutory accounts, IFRS and local GAAP.</p></div>
        <div style="padding:24px;background:#FDFAF6;border:1px solid #E2DDD6;border-radius:2px"><h4 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px">GCC &amp; Middle East</h4><p style="font-size:14px;color:#6B7280;line-height:1.65">UAE corporate tax, VAT registration and returns, free zone and mainland compliance. Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Bahrain.</p></div>
        <div style="padding:24px;background:#FDFAF6;border:1px solid #E2DDD6;border-radius:2px"><h4 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px">Asia Pacific</h4><p style="font-size:14px;color:#6B7280;line-height:1.65">Singapore GST and corporate tax, Hong Kong profits tax, Malaysia, India, Vietnam, and other APAC jurisdictions.</p></div>
        <div style="padding:24px;background:#FDFAF6;border:1px solid #E2DDD6;border-radius:2px"><h4 style="font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px">Latin America</h4><p style="font-size:14px;color:#6B7280;line-height:1.65">Mexico, Colombia, Brazil, Chile, Panama, and Uruguay. Local GAAP, transfer pricing, and tax compliance.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--cream" style="border-top:1px solid #E2DDD6">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal">Related Guides</span>
      <h2 class="reveal">Go Deeper</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule reveal"></div>
      <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:40px">
        <a class="card reveal" href="/insights/uae-corporate-tax-vat" style="display:block;text-decoration:none">
          <span class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:14px">UAE · Tax</span>
          <h3>UAE Corporate Tax &amp; VAT</h3>
          <p>The 9% rate and AED 375,000 threshold, free-zone QFZP rules, the 5% VAT and registration thresholds.</p>
          <span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold)">Read the guide →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="card reveal reveal-delay-1" href="/insights" style="display:block;text-decoration:none">
          <span class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:14px">By Country</span>
          <h3>Company Formation &amp; Tax by Country</h3>
          <p>Corporate tax, VAT and the local regimes for Germany, Switzerland, Belgium, Georgia, Saudi Arabia and the UAE.</p>
          <span style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold)">View all →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <h2 class="reveal">Discuss Your Compliance Requirements</h2>
    <p class="reveal reveal-delay-1">Tell us which jurisdictions you operate in and what your current compliance arrangements look like. We will map the gaps and propose a coordinated solution.</p>
    <div class="btn-row reveal reveal-delay-2">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Schedule a Consultation →</a>
      <a href="/insights" class="btn-secondary">Read Our Insights</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={`{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "name": "Accounting, Tax & Compliance", "serviceType": "Accounting, Tax & Compliance", "description": "Accounting, corporate tax, VAT and ongoing compliance across jurisdictions.", "provider": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "ARM Management", "url": "https://arm-management.com"}, "areaServed": ["European Union", "GCC & Middle East", "Asia-Pacific", "Latin America"], "url": "https://arm-management.com/services/accounting-tax"}`} />
</Base>
